# 4. 逃げた、その先は

Mizuki: Hmm...
Mizuki: (Yeah, less of this effect and more motion might give this part a bigger punch.)
Mizuki: (I'll try animating that asset Ena sent me yesterday a little more and...)
Mizuki: That should do it. I'll try playing it from the beginning...
Mizuki: Hey, not bad...! I'll have Kanade and the others take a look at this.
Mizuki: (Still, thank goodness...)
Mizuki: (I'm so glad Mafuyu chose to run away...)
Mizuki: (I was so worried since it really seemed like the walls were closing in on her.)
Mizuki: (So, I'm really glad what I said ended up helping her a little.)
Mizuki: (Unfortunately, running away doesn't do anything about solving the root cause of her problems...)
Mizuki: (I'm sure a lot of stuff's going through her mind right now...)
Mizuki: (And I need to start thinking about what's gonna happen moving forward.)
Mizuki: (After all, I'm partly responsible for her running since I was the one who suggested it to her...)
Mizuki: Still...
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: What more can I do for her? I mean, I still haven't been able to deal with my own problems after running away.
Mizuki: I should take a quick break... My eyes are starting to hurt after staring at this screen for so long.
Mizuki: I know! I can go see if that ribbon I found the other day looks good on Rin.
Mizuki: (That should help take my mind off things...)
Mizuki: Let's see. Where's Rin...?
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: Hey, MEIKO!
MEIKO: Mizuki? What are you doing here...?
Mizuki: I came looking for Rin. Do you know where she is?
MEIKO: Rin's gone somewhere a bit far away.
Mizuki: Far away?
MEIKO: Yes, there's a new area in SEKAI now.
Mizuki: Wait, what new area?
Mizuki: You've got me curious now. Maybe I should go check it out.
MEIKO: Did something happen...?
Mizuki: Huh? Wh-Why do you ask?
MEIKO: You're not acting like your usual self...
MEIKO: Is something bothering you...?
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: Hmm... Well...
Mizuki: It isn't bothering me per se, but it is kinda bugging me...
MEIKO: What's bugging you...?
Mizuki: Oh, um... I was thinking about how relieved I am that Mafuyu decided to run away.
Mizuki: And she seems to be doing a lot better now that she's in Kanade's care.
MEIKO: Right.
Mizuki: *Nod*
Mizuki: So, all of that made me realize that I need to keep supporting her. After all, I'm the one who said it's okay for her to run...
Mizuki: But...
Mizuki: I don't really know what to do since I've never gone past this point...
MEIKO: This point...?
Mizuki: Yeah, I don't know what you're supposed to do after you've made a run for it...
MEIKO: ...
Mizuki: Running is only a temporary solution, right? You have to deal with your problems eventually.
Mizuki: But I haven't actually done that yet...
Mizuki: That's why I'm not really sure if there's anything more I can do for Mafuyu...
MEIKO: If you don't know, then face them.
Mizuki: Huh...?
MEIKO: If you don't know what to do after running, then stop running and face your problems.
Mizuki: ...!
Mizuki: But that means...
MEIKO: I know. That's easier said than done.
MEIKO: But if you truly do wish to help Mafuyu, then this may be the best time for you to do that.
MEIKO: By doing so, you may learn something new. It could be the very thing that she needs to hear.
MEIKO: Like what you told her the other day.
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (Yeah, I was able to make that suggestion because of what I went through...)
Mizuki: (So, now that we've both run... If there is something new I can learn by actually facing my problems...)
Mizuki: (Plus, there's...)
Mizuki: (I've been asking so much of Ena...)
Mizuki: (She's been waiting for me ever since that day...)
Mizuki: (I don't know if I'm really ready for this...)
Mizuki: (I really don't know, but...)
Mizuki: Thanks, MEIKO...
Mizuki: I feel a little better now after talking to you.
MEIKO: Really? Then, good for you...
